Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.71,0:23:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are some very famous people\Non current television
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.36,0:23:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,talk shows,\N130 to 160.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.73,0:23:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Their chances of being happy are around 12%.\NSo, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.01,0:23:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The rate of happiness, then,\Nis not due to something out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.85,0:23:21.83,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's due to what you have\Nbecome. So you can
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.83,0:23:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,be happy under miserable circumstances\Nand commit suicide
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.72,0:23:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in the midst of luxury.\NSo the rate of
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.14,0:23:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness, then, is a direct\Nresult of one's level
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.24,0:23:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness.\NAs you move up, you need less and less.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.16,0:23:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,You want less and less.\NSomebody says, is there anything you want
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.29,0:23:45.24,Default,,0,0,0,,today?\NNo.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.91,0:23:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything you need. I got it.\NSo what you need and have,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.64,0:24:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you got already.\NSo the chance of being happy, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.11,0:24:03.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is pretty good.\NAll right. So we'll move on.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.05,0:24:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want nothing,\Nthen you get along
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.00,0:24:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,with less and less.\NYou get along with less and less.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.27,0:24:15.81,Default,,0,0,0,,When I first came out here, as I told you,\NI had a six-pack of Pepsi and a piece of cheese in the fridge
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.81,0:24:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and celebrated Saturday night\Nby splitting an apple with a friend of mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.06,0:24:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I said,\Ntonight we'll have an apple. Oh, wow, he says.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.33,0:24:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Big time, have an apple.\NAll right. So now we'll get to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.94,0:24:36.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the actual subject for today.\NWhat is truth?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.24,0:24:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Truth is different than\Nthe last lecture was on reality,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:41.96,0:24:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,which is linear\Nand has to do with facts.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.46,0:24:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Has to do with facts. Provable facts.\NTruth, as you can see,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.48,0:24:53.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is more abstract.\NMore abstract. It's more than
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.53,0:25:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,just a fact.\NTruth is a more
Dialogue: 0,0:25:00.13,0:25:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,abstract notion\Nwith sort of philosophic,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.97,0:25:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,metaphysical overtones.\NHuh?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.05,0:25:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,First,\Nthe first thing we notice
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.66,0:25:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in the great books of the Western world,\NI mentioned Descartes,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:15.25,0:25:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,who pointed out the difference between\Nperception and essence
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.88,0:25:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,between the lamb\Nand the sheep and the wolf.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.00,0:25:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,He said,\NDescartes,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.07,0:25:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the problem is the difference\Nbetween res interna and res
Dialogue: 0,0:25:32.36,0:25:36.17,Default,,0,0,0,,externa, meaning\Nthe world as you see it
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.17,0:25:39.45,Default,,0,0,0,,as compared to the world\Nas it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.60,0:25:46.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's a barrier there between.\NSo the capacity to see what actually is,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.60,0:25:52.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is limited and relatively unusual.\NMost people go by opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:52.30,0:25:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Res interna, that is my idea of the world,\Nthe way I see the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.21,0:26:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, that's the famous argument\Nreferred to in Plato.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.01,0:26:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Protagoras says, well, the world I see is my reality\Nand the world that you see is your reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.79,0:26:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And then he made the incorrect assumption.\NTherefore, there is no ultimate reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.79,0:26:19.79,Default,,0,0,0,,He should have said,\Nwhich proves that I am dumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.79,0:26:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And the fact that people have different opinions\Ndoesn't mean there's different realities.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.14,0:26:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just different perceptions.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:31.64,0:26:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.\NSocrates' dictum is all that any spiritual student needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.97,0:26:44.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates' dictum was that man chooses\Nonly the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.02,0:26:48.99,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's just that he doesn't know\Nhow to comprehend the difference between the real good
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.99,0:26:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,and the illusory good.\NBut every man is choosing the good.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.27,0:26:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you think it's good to blow you all up,\Nthen that's his idea of good.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.51,0:27:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Good is killing all such people because you're all infidels.\NSo to be able to forgive would require, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.55,0:27:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,a recognition of that inner reality,\Nthat each person is seeking what
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.27,0:27:18.27,Default,,0,0,0,,they believe to be the good and, therefore,\Ncapable of salvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.27,0:27:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?\NIn today's world, however, popularity
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.48,0:27:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,reigns and the herd instinct, the media bias,\Nand, of course, the memes, which are the repeated phrases that
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.53,0:27:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,are repeated often enough.\NIf you take a lie and repeat it often enough,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.64,0:27:47.01,Default,,0,0,0,,people will believe it.\NPeople will believe a lie if you just repeat it often enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.01,0:27:53.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, oh, no, I wouldn't do that.\NYes, you will, under experimental conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.50,0:27:57.49,Default,,0,0,0,,By the end of the experiment, I'll\Nhave you convinced that your front is your back
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.49,0:28:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,and your back is your front.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.24,0:28:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, the world's great dictators\Nhave depended on this, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.38,0:28:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Media bias.\NAnd, of course, the extraordinary popular
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.11,0:28:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Delusions and the Madness of Crowds\Nby Mackie.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.88,0:28:25.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It was written, I don't know, in the late 1700s, I think.\NGives examples of how the whole world believes a certain thing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.50,0:28:32.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and it turns out to be illusion.\NAnd, of course, he used the tulip craze in Holland.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.63,0:28:37.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I like this because you say, well, everybody\Ncouldn't be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.24,0:28:45.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Certainly, global warming is due to man,\Nextraordinary popular delusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.79,0:28:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody believes that.\NIt's man that causes global warming.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.07,0:29:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, yeah.\NAll right, so everybody believes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.96,0:29:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a popular delusion.\NEverybody believes it, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.01,0:29:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's due to the slant.\NIt's due to ignoring the fact that these things are,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.61,0:29:18.40,Default,,0,0,0,,that the temperature of the Earth,\Nit reflects the magnetic activity
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.40,0:29:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,on the surface of the sun for tens of thousands of years.\NAnd what man is doing is contributing contamination,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.64,0:29:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,contamination.\NBut contamination is not warming, global warming.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.68,0:29:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If you fly over the United States,\Nyou quickly leave the populated area.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.15,0:29:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And you then fly for hours and hours over nothingness,\Nthousands and thousands of miles of nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.41,0:29:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no people there creating pollution.\NSo pollution is caused by people,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.36,0:29:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and global warming is due to something else.\NAll right, so that makes you a heretic, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.28,0:30:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Very people.\NFew people care to be a heretic and considered a madman.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.28,0:30:09.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because of political slant.\NSo in our world, truth is overridden by political slant.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.01,0:30:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And as Bush said, money trumps peace, right?\NMoney trumps peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.54,0:30:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Politics and money, then, dominate our society.\NSo the confusion of truth with these previous things
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.65,0:30:31.15,Default,,0,0,0,,is that it's confused with opinion and faith and belief\Nsystems and data, which is often false.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.15,0:30:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Secondhand smoke is also another illusion.\NAnd the federal court actually threw it out
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.91,0:30:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,as stupid junk science.\NSmoking's bad for you, but secondhand smoke
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.69,0:30:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,has no bad effect whatsoever.\NSo anyway, that makes you a heretic, you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.66,0:30:58.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because the ordinary popular delusions has people convinced.\NAnd this has to do with the fact that we're not going to be
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.98,0:31:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,able to get rid of the fact that these studies are well funded.\NSo if I want to get some money out of the government,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:08.99,0:31:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I just conjure up something.\NThe secondhand smoke causes schizophrenia, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.16,0:31:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll get the money.\NIf I put out a paper that secondhand smoke is not
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.01,0:31:27.53,Default,,0,0,0,,related to schizophrenia, you won't get any money.\NSo political slant, then, influences science, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.53,0:31:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So political slant, then, influences science, you know?\NSo political slant, then, influences science, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.83,0:31:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what we mean by falsified data.\NFalsified data, I could give you better selections
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.69,0:31:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,of falsified data, which the medical world doesn't even\Nknow, and the world doesn't even know.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.34,0:31:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll say, well, a certain treatment only\Nworks 5% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.78,0:31:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's worthless.\NOr another treatment only works 50% of the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.64,0:32:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's worthless.\NWhat they fail to see is from that selected population, the 5%
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.39,0:32:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,is 100% of that group.\NIf you know how to select in the group,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.82,0:32:15.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the recovery rate is 100%.\NIf I tell people who are depressed,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.09,0:32:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,stop eating sugar and sweets,\Nstop eating sugar and sweets,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.64,0:32:23.03,Default,,0,0,0,,probably 40% will recover.\NLet's see how many will recover.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.74,0:32:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If we take people that walk into the clinic,\Nthey're depressed,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.25,0:32:33.70,Default,,0,0,0,,over 30% of function hypoglycemia,\N35%, 40%.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.70,0:32:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so about 35% of people\Nwill recover from depression
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.18,0:32:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,if they stop eating sugar and sweets.\NSo in that subgroup,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.72,0:32:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,your recovery rate is 100%.\NSo you can't say sugar-free diets are worthless.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.86,0:32:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you try them in a large group of people,\Nyou'll get a small recovery,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.84,0:32:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the population at large.\NBut amongst the select group,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.49,0:33:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,your recovery rate is 100%.\NSo the clinician is one who can intuit
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.63,0:33:10.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and by lots of experience over many years,\Nsort of get which group
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.14,0:33:11.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to choose.\NWhich this person falls into, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.53,0:33:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Which one he falls into.\NAnd when I used to get appointments made by phone,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.33,0:33:21.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd say stop eating sugar and sweets\Nand take a lot of vitamin B3
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.77,0:33:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and I'll see you in a week, see?\NAnd about half the time,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.26,0:33:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,by the time they walked into the office,\NI'd say, I don't know why I'm here, doc.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.21,0:33:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It's cool now.\NAnxiety attacks and depression
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.00,0:33:37.74,Default,,0,0,0,,are very often functional hypoglycemia.\NThe body puts out too much insulin.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.33,0:33:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so you want to avoid things\Nthat create insulin.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.66,0:33:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you switch from glucose and sucrose to fructose,\Nthe hypoglycemia goes away.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.11,0:33:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Fruit sugar does not stimulate an insulin response.\NSo you see, it doesn't cost anything at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.61,0:34:01.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The cost to the taxpayer is nothing.\NAnd the likelihood of success is extremely high
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.25,0:34:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,if you know how to pick the subgroup.\NSo I'm just pointing out the source,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.64,0:34:10.09,Default,,0,0,0,,the fallacies of data.\NThe data will say that, well, this is no good.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.09,0:34:14.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It only cures 10%.\NBut that 10%, the cure rate is 100.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.78,0:34:21.40,Default,,0,0,0,,It's an historic human deficiency,\Nthe incapacity to tell truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.40,0:34:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,We now corroborate truth by calibration.\NSo for the first time really in history,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.88,0:34:33.05,Default,,0,0,0,,we have an objective means of verifying truth.\NAnd as you can see from that previous diagram,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.84,0:34:38.84,Default,,0,0,0,,truth is dependent on context,\Nand understanding of truth is level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.03,0:34:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To truly know a thing is actually to be aware.\NTo know a thing is to be aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.80,0:34:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than to know about it.\NSo lots of people know about certain subjects,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.71,0:34:50.80,Default,,0,0,0,,but to know it, you have to become it.\NYou have to become it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.84,0:34:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,To know, you know about hermits,\Nbut unless you're a hermit,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.23,0:35:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't know what it is to be a hermit.\NIt's very hermity to be a hermit, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.55,0:35:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,In our society, you have the impact of the media,\Nwhich is enormous,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.98,0:35:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and caters to narcissism.\NAnd narcissism, what is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.96,0:35:18.09,Default,,0,0,0,,It's projectionism.\NIt's projected self-interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.09,0:35:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, you've already salted the mind,\Nyou've already decided on the outcome,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.09,0:35:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and now you go back and cite some incident.\NThis typifies our current society,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.09,0:35:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is almost 100% narcissistic.\NAlmost 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.38,0:35:35.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost 100%.\NAlmost 100%.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.61,0:35:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Media are completely narcissistic.\NEverything is sold.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.80,0:35:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,The Me Tube, the iTube, the YouTube.\NYou're in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.92,0:35:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,You're in nature.\NYou're in nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.15,0:36:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,YouTube, there's only Me Tube.\NSo narcissism is self-interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.38,0:36:06.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And the bias that comes across is just constant.\NAnd if you're aligned with truth and integrity
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.42,0:36:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and logic,\Nit's just very difficult listening to the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.42,0:36:18.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because almost every single political statement\Nis distorted.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.42,0:36:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Almost every political statement leaves out\Na key word that would totally change your picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.42,0:36:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why they purposely leave that out.\NYeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.44,0:36:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,So a projected self-interest.\NYou could say, why is everybody so interested
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.82,0:36:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that the whole world should agree with them\Nand that the world should go along with what they think?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.21,0:36:43.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I mean?\NI mean, what's the gain?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.25,0:36:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the gain?\NWhat's the gain?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.46,0:36:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't any.\NIt feeds on itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.46,0:36:55.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Narcissism feeds on itself.\NIf everybody agrees with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.75,0:37:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,now your sense of importance goes up.\NSo it's your sense of importance
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.75,0:37:05.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that dominate the field.\NIt creates a sense of self-interest.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.75,0:37:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In the animal world,\Ndominate brings about survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.75,0:37:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In the animal world,\Nit doesn't necessarily lead to survival at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.88,0:37:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It very often leads to its opposite.\NNarcissism distorts.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.88,0:37:27.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Projected self-interest.\NAnd all you get out of it is a sense of grandiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.51,0:37:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,A sense of grandiosity.\NIf everybody agrees with my research,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.09,0:37:36.09,Default,,0,0,0,,then I'm a great and happy person.\NAnd if they don't,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.09,0:37:41.09,Default,,0,0,0,,then I'm a miserable failure, right?\NI mean, that's the way the ego works.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.09,0:37:45.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So people then want to propagate\Ntheir own belief systems on others
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.09,0:37:51.15,Default,,0,0,0,,because they get an immediate payoff.\NEverybody has to think the way they think.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.15,0:37:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,All mentation, however,\Nreflects a limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.80,0:38:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The mind is really unable, by its design,\Nto be able to discern truth from falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.40,0:38:11.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The brain is like a hardware of the computer.\NAnd the mentation is like the software.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.40,0:38:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All mentation reflects limitation.\NSo whatever you think is already a limitation.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.94,0:38:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever you think.\NIt's what you are
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.50,0:38:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,that transcends the limitation.\NThe capacity to know truth is already limited,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.53,0:38:41.69,Default,,0,0,0,,as you can see from the diagram on brain physiology,\Nthat brain function itself
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.69,0:38:46.69,Default,,0,0,0,,limits the capacity to understand\Nand comprehend reality and truth
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.69,0:38:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,amongst people that are below 200.\NHalf the population, therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.94,0:38:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,is frankly, intrinsically,\Nby virtue of brain physiology,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.23,0:39:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,unable to comprehend abstract truth,\Nanything 200 and up.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.23,0:39:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And that has to do with context.\NSo the errors that you see
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.84,0:39:14.15,Default,,0,0,0,,day after day after day on the television\Nhas to do with this limitation of brain function,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.15,0:39:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,of calibration levels below 200,\Nwho have their own heroes
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.51,0:39:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and political parties and belief systems\Nand their own cheering sections.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.51,0:39:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They have their own block sites.\NThe worst block site I know of calibrates at 90.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:35.55,0:39:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And it sort of specializes in hatred.\NSpecializes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:41.57,0:39:44.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't even tell you the name,\Nbut it's so awful,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.73,0:39:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want you to even glance at it.\NSpecializing in hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.90,0:39:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Specializing in hatred, you can see.\NNow what could people get out of putting
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.90,0:39:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,all that hateful stuff on there?\NAll of it lies, all of it hateful,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.90,0:40:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,all of it derogatory,\Nall of it fallacious.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.90,0:40:06.86,Default,,0,0,0,,What could a person get out of that?\NThey get being who they are.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.86,0:40:12.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The naivete, the human mind.\NOr I was saying, what's their motive?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.94,0:40:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Folks, they don't have any motive.\NWe're the few people on the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.32,0:40:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand this.\NThey don't have any motive at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.28,0:40:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,There isn't a motive.\NThere's a guy named, what was his name, KOS,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.61,0:40:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,that killed all the people in some university\Nand had a hate video that he put on
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.84,0:40:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,and he just ranted hate.\NWasn't he the Virginia Tech killer or somebody?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.48,0:40:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Lowest I've ever calibrated.\NFive.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.07,0:40:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Five.\NPeople say, well, he must have had a troubled childhood.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.82,0:41:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,His mother must have had a troubled childhood.\NWhat's the motive of a serial killer?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.82,0:41:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the motive behind wickedness?\NThere isn't any.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:15.98,0:41:20.23,Default,,0,0,0,,They're just being what they are.\NThere's no motive.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.23,0:41:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no bad childhood\Nthat caused their resentment,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.23,0:41:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,that caused maybe so-and-so,\Nand if we just get them a good therapist,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.23,0:41:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,he'll be okay.\NAs one of those people,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.44,0:41:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,what would I do with a therapist?\NI'd kill them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.78,0:41:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,They deserve to die\Nbecause they're saying there's something wrong with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.57,0:41:57.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So I will have to kill them.\NWhy?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.40,0:42:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's who I am.\NIdentity defines essence.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:02.46,0:42:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them the story about the frog.\NThe frog and something rides on his back.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.09,0:42:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Who rides on his back?\NTell us the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.90,0:42:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, the scorpion rides on the back of the frog.\NWasn't that it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.36,0:42:36.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell them the story.\NCome on, tell them that story.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.65,0:42:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I demand it.\NI can't remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.50,0:42:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It's been so long since I told you.\NTell me that story.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.50,0:42:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How does that go?\NThere was a frog and a scorpion,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.50,0:42:50.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and the scorpion went across the pond.\NSo he got on top of the back of the frog.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:50.50,0:42:53.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NAnd as they're going across the pond,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.69,0:42:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,the scorpion, he says,\Nnow, you will not sting me, will you?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:57.75,0:42:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And the scorpion says,\Nno, I won't sting you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.75,0:43:01.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I won't sting you.\NAnd they're going across the pond,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.75,0:43:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and all of a sudden,\Nthe scorpion stings the frog.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.75,0:43:06.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, he's dying,\Nand he says,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.75,0:43:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,you said you wouldn't sting me.\NHe says, why'd you sting me?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.75,0:43:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And he goes,\Nthat's because that's what I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.84,0:43:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.\NThat's what people don't get.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:16.07,0:43:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I am a scorpion.\NThat's why.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.61,0:43:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That's because that's what I am.\NSo you see,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.03,0:43:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,in dealing with,\Nin dealing with people and political systems
Dialogue: 0,0:43:31.36,0:43:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,which wish to extinguish you,\Nextinguish you all,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.36,0:43:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody in here is an infidel.\NEverybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.67,0:43:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You all deserve to die.\NThat's the proclamation
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.80,0:43:49.01,Default,,0,0,0,,of America's enemies right now.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.01,0:43:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Is there a motive?\NNot really.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.86,0:44:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because that's what that energy does\Nand how it sees the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:00.65,0:44:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't say it's anybody's fault,\Nnor do I wish to blame anybody at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:06.03,0:44:10.26,Default,,0,0,0,,But it,\Nsometimes spiritual alignment
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.26,0:44:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,leads to a naivete and a denial\Nand sort of a wimpism
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.98,0:44:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,that's supposed to be peace marches and all.\NBest thing to do, folks,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.05,0:44:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,with a peace march\Nis to blow them the hell up.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.67,0:44:41.96,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NTo call a spade a spade
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.96,0:44:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is not politically popular in today's world\Nwhere euphemisms are used to distort images
Dialogue: 0,0:44:50.86,0:44:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and cover up the underlying reality.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.86,0:45:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So we'll go to the next slide.\NSo what we believe to be truth
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.46,0:45:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,is subject to programming\Nand indoctrination.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.46,0:45:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course,\None of the dangers of today's world
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.61,0:45:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is the indoctrination of the youth\Nof other people,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.61,0:45:14.61,Default,,0,0,0,,other cultures\Nthat are out to kill us.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.61,0:45:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NProgramming and indoctrination.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.67,0:45:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And today's,\Nthis week's news
Dialogue: 0,0:45:20.80,0:45:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is the Mickey Mouse cartoon\Ncurrently in Islam.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.84,0:45:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Mickey Mouse\Nfor a long time
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.84,0:45:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,just shouted,\Nshouted Haiti of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:29.84,0:45:33.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But Mickey Mouse became\Nliked by the children
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.84,0:45:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,over in those Islamic societies.\NAnd in the last edition
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.84,0:45:42.84,Default,,0,0,0,,a week ago,\Nthe Israelis murdered Mickey Mouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.84,0:45:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So the news media\Nall over now
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.84,0:45:49.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is how horrible\NAmericans and Israelis
Dialogue: 0,0:45:49.84,0:45:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and all are.\NThey murdered,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:51.84,0:45:54.84,Default,,0,0,0,,they slaughtered him.\NThey murdered Mickey Mouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.84,0:46:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If I was some little kid\Nin another culture
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.28,0:46:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,and watched Mickey Mouse\Nbeing slaughtered,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:05.28,0:46:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I would hate those people,\Nwouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.46,0:46:09.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo that's,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.46,0:46:11.46,Default,,0,0,0,,that's inculcated hatred,\Ninculcated hatred.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.46,0:46:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And Nazi propaganda minister Goebbels\Nwas the world's best at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.46,0:46:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He compared Jews to worms\Nand mice and rats
Dialogue: 0,0:46:21.73,0:46:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and things like this.\NAnd he did it visually.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.73,0:46:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So a picture,\Nyou've already been programmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:27.73,0:46:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I just want you to get\Nhow fast your mind is programmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.07,0:46:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you see that picture,\Nyou just got programmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.07,0:46:37.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You say, nobody's programming me.\NYou've already been programmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.21,0:46:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got programmed.\NAll I have to do
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.42,0:46:43.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is one image of that.\NYou just had it.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.42,0:46:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You just got imprinted\Nwith that image.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:48.71,0:46:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.90,0:46:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the chances of arriving\Nat a capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.90,0:46:54.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to discern truth\Nand stand for truth
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.90,0:46:57.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and live a life of truth,\Nyou see how slim it is
Dialogue: 0,0:46:57.90,0:47:01.90,Default,,0,0,0,,in today's world\Nunder the sheer media barrage.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.90,0:47:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So the human mind\Nis subject to programming
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.98,0:47:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and constant indoctrination,\Nconstant indoctrination.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:09.98,0:47:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth is different than,\Ntruth has to do with
Dialogue: 0,0:47:15.21,0:47:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,what does the thing mean.\NYou can define a thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.21,0:47:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you can give its linear definition,\Nbut then,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.21,0:47:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,what does it mean?\NSo that brings us
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.34,0:47:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to the hermeneutics of abstraction.\NHermeneutics.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.40,0:47:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the science\Nor philosophy of meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.40,0:47:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What does a thing mean?\NHermeneutics.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:30.40,0:47:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember I discussed\Nthe problematic hermeneutics
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.53,0:47:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,of relativistic epistemology?\NI've never gotten a blog
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.53,0:47:38.38,Default,,0,0,0,,or an email\Ncriticizing me for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:39.38,0:47:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a one\Nhas ever contested.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.38,0:47:45.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes,\Nthen I get an answer,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.26,0:47:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but I don't know\Nwhat the answer is.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.26,0:47:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know\Nwhat the answer is.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:51.05,0:47:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know\Nwhat the answer is.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.05,0:47:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes,\Nthen I get a nasty email.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:56.05,0:47:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I said,\Nwell,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:58.05,0:48:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find that out\Nif you study the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:02.11,0:48:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,problematic\Nhermeneutics
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.11,0:48:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,of relativistic epistemology.\NYeah,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:07.11,0:48:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,that's right.\NYou can't criticize a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.30,0:48:11.30,Default,,0,0,0,,until you understand it.\NThat doesn't keep
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.30,0:48:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,bloggers from off there.\NI don't know
Dialogue: 0,0:48:14.76,0:48:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,what they do with themselves\Nall evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.76,0:48:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I say that,\Nbut to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.76,0:48:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,a blogger is somebody\Nwho reads something
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.76,0:48:22.76,Default,,0,0,0,,they don't like\Nand they just go,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.76,0:48:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,snort.\NWell,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.86,0:48:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,if you,\Nyou dumb AA,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.86,0:48:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,which immediately gets\Npicked on everybody's
Dialogue: 0,0:48:33.82,0:48:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,blog site\Nand quoted.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.48,0:48:39.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nyou can't criticize
Dialogue: 0,0:48:39.73,0:48:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,the thing\Nunless you can first
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.73,0:48:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,comprehend it.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.73,0:48:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,when people criticize\Nsome things I've written,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.73,0:48:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll say,\Nfirst read the book,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.73,0:48:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,then let me hear it from you.\NAnd when we use
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.03,0:48:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the RMI,\Nwe ask,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.03,0:48:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,do they read the book?\NWe always got to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:55.73,0:48:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,All the people\Nwho criticize it,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.28,0:49:00.50,Default,,0,0,0,,over 2%\Nhave read it.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.50,0:49:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Over 3%,\N5%,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.88,0:49:05.59,Default,,0,0,0,,4%,\N3%,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.59,0:49:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,3%\Nhave at least
Dialogue: 0,0:49:08.17,0:49:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,tried to read the book.\NIt's hard reading,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.17,0:49:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I know.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.17,0:49:15.80,Default,,0,0,0,,meaning,\Nand we know
Dialogue: 0,0:49:15.80,0:49:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what the fact,\Nwe know
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.17,0:49:20.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what the facts are,\Nand we know
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.17,0:49:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,what the truth is,\Nbut what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.17,0:49:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?\NWhat's the implication?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:24.17,0:49:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nwhen you talk
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.17,0:49:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,about meaning,\Nyou're talking
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.17,0:49:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,about now levels\Nof abstraction.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.17,0:49:32.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What does\Nit mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.17,0:49:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Well,\Nit means
Dialogue: 0,0:49:34.17,0:49:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,it's one thing\Nto this
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.30,0:49:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,or that,\Nbut what does it
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.30,0:49:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,actually mean?\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:41.13,0:49:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the\Ncapacity
Dialogue: 0,0:49:43.69,0:49:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,for abstraction.\NNow,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.82,0:49:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200,\Nthe people
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.82,0:49:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,do not have\Nthe capacity
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.82,0:49:51.98,Default,,0,0,0,,for abstraction.\NThey are,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.98,0:49:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,deal only\Nin the pedestrian,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.98,0:49:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,limited\Nidea
Dialogue: 0,0:49:55.98,0:49:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,of causality,\Nreductive
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.98,0:50:00.13,Default,,0,0,0,,materialism.\NSo,
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.13,0:50:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,if it's not\Nprovable
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.13,0:50:04.13,Default,,0,0,0,,within a very\Nlimited
Dialogue: 0,0:50:04.13,0:50:06.13,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigm,\Nthen it's
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.13,0:50:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,fallacious.\NAnd you know
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.19,0:50:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that famous\Nguy that was
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.57,0:50:12.57,Default,,0,0,0,,in the\NPhoenix newspaper
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.57,0:50:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that's written\Nfour or five
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.57,0:50:16.57,Default,,0,0,0,,books claiming\Nthat Einstein
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.57,0:50:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,is a fraud.\NAnd he keeps
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.57,0:50:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,writing more\Nbooks about
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.57,0:50:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Einstein being\Na fraud.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.57,0:50:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,What he doesn't\Nget is that
