Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.55,0:52:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,tension\Nset
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.96,0:52:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,live one day at a time, you know. Forgive and forget. Live one day at a time. Easy does it.\NLive and let live. Paddle your own canoe. Instead of trying to paddle others. So
Dialogue: 0,0:52:22.50,0:52:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,this becomes a mental habit, a mental habit, and it influences probability,\Nwhereas mathematically the probability is of a different dimension. Once the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.76,0:52:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,attention set begins to set in, probability is that you're going to pick\Na peaceful solution more and more often. Also you will not be happy with the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.98,0:52:56.67,Default,,0,0,0,,resentment. You may get over resentment, you may juice it for a little while, but\Neventually you find that you don't like living with it. So instead of getting
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.67,0:53:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,even with the person, what you do is say, I can see that that person just couldn't\Nknow any better at the time, at the time. In the situation area, and that's the way
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.55,0:53:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,it seemed to them, it seemed to them, you know, that they\Nshould get even with you, or get that parking space, or whatever it is. Buy the
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.46,0:53:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,last copy of, what's the name of the book that's out now? Harry Potter. Get to the\Nbookstore, the last Harry Potter just got sold out. So attention set then
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.40,0:53:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,influences our habitual choice, and we favor that which is more and more\Npeaceful and loving. So peacefulness and lovingness then give it to be habitual.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.78,0:53:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why people say what can I do for world peace and to solve the world's\Nproblems, etc. And I would say to be as loving as possible towards all that
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.92,0:54:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,exists, and to walk over the little black beetle instead of squishing him. You're\Nalready serving God in the world by saving his little life, because out of
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.84,0:54:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,compassion you don't want to extinguish life unless you're actually forced to. So\Nthe influence of attention set is actually a
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.26,0:54:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,physiologic,\Nneurologic phenomena so by consistently making certain choices your neurologic
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.21,0:54:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,set your neurologic propensities the way the neurons are being to fire begin to\Nfire more and more favorably in a certain direction the more often you
Dialogue: 0,0:54:36.50,0:54:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,pick something negative the more likely it is you're going to pick the negative\Nagain and we notice that negative human behaviors tend to be rather fixed the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.34,0:55:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,way to pick up a criminal is to stop any car on the road at night that has a\Ntaillight out any couple theta the sign of a criminal is a taillights out why
Dialogue: 0,0:55:05.07,0:55:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,because that's the whole lifestyle and it's a dead giveaway and hitchhikers on\Nthe highway it's the same so attention set then influences choice now the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:21.55,0:55:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,context of the problem is that the way you pick up a criminal is to stop any\Ncontent is subject to context and part of context is time and history before you
