Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.07,0:55:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,because they were running for president whatever if you're ready for president\Nthen you can buy anything you're running for public office you can lie about
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.34,0:55:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,anything and everybody says well I don't know I don't know I don't know I don't\Nknow but you'll be funny when you get here like to do this yes that's the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.98,0:56:10.73,Default,,0,0,0,,context of the problem and so you just have to look it over the history and\Nyou'll be funny when you get here you'll be funny and you'll be funny yeah
Dialogue: 0,0:56:10.73,0:56:21.01,Default,,0,0,0,,what does that exactly mean to do so you're trying to do this on the right\Npath and all of a sudden if you're standing on the road you just have to
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.01,0:56:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,listen you're just going to say this is not the right path you're not gonna do\Nit and you're going to have to deal with it and you're gonna have to think about
Dialogue: 0,0:56:25.09,0:56:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,not subject to time or circumstances.\NWhat is intrinsically so and true forever through all time?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.44,0:56:41.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You might say that God is the creator of the universe,\Nis so under all circumstances for all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.42,0:56:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that every hair on your head should be counted is true.\NWhether you believe it or not is different,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.98,0:56:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,but the truth is not subject to circumstances.\NLet's just reconfirm that one because I like that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.73,0:57:02.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You're responsible.\NEvery hair on your head should be counted.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.69,0:57:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.\NSee?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.26,0:57:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why it's risky to trust people who don't believe in God\Nbecause people who believe in God know they're accountable.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.21,0:57:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Judgment day will arrive, et cetera.\NPeople who don't believe in God, what's the consequences of lying?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.30,0:57:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing.\NIf a person doesn't believe in God, why not lie?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.34,0:57:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You should lie.\NThere are whole cultures that tell you that you should lie,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:35.59,0:57:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you don't lie, you get beaten when you get home.\NYou're supposed to tell the tourists that this is a genuine antique
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.40,0:57:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and get $50 for it.\NIt's mass produced.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.03,0:57:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It costs them $1.50.\NBut if you don't convince them that it's a real antique and get $50,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:54.92,0:58:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you actually get beaten when you get home, right?\NSo that's a different kind of a culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:03.21,0:58:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not answerable to God at all,\Nand therefore you can say and do anything you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:11.76,0:58:18.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can't really trust on a certain level.\NYou can trust their likelihood of their behaving a certain way,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.92,0:58:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,but in the ultimate, you can't really trust\Nbecause if you're not accountable to God for your behavior,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.67,0:58:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,then you're only into pragmatic using others.\NSo Werner had a very interesting definition,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.48,0:58:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and I remembered it all those years.\NI forget when Werner was around.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.88,0:58:44.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Back in the early 70s, I think.\NWasn't it early 70s?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:44.61,0:58:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,71, 72?\NEverybody did Est.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.86,0:58:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a great experience.\NIt got people.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:53.21,0:59:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The purpose of Est was to get people over 200,\Nto stop giving alibis, to stop being fake,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:01.11,0:59:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,and accept the fact that, yeah, you are,\Nyou are a rotten father, or you're a bum teacher.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.28,0:59:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact.\NStop pretending you're a big star.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:09.96,0:59:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\NWhat is so all the time everywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.71,0:59:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So there is a statement that's independent of context\Nand timing and sequence.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.63,0:59:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Truth then brings up the subjective and experiential\Nthat's within versus that which is demonstrable.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.19,0:59:40.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So truth can be an existent reality,\Nbut it's subjective and not provable.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.69,0:59:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience of the mystic is not provable.\NIt's confirmable by consciousness calibration,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.71,0:59:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's not provable.\NSo the subjective and the experiential
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.26,1:00:00.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is a whole different field of reality,\Nreality and truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.36,1:00:09.96,Default,,0,0,0,,from that which is demonstrable and linear.\NThis brings up paradigm allegiance.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.96,1:00:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,People become confined to a certain stratosphere,\Nyou might, a certain content, context rather,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.78,1:00:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,in which they try to corral all their,\Ntheir understandings of everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:31.67,1:00:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,They try to put it in a certain paradigm.\NThe pedestrian, materialistic reductionism,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:40.67,1:00:46.73,Default,,0,0,0,,which deals with provable content in the notorious sense,\Nwhich deals with content in the Newtonian paradigm,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.73,1:00:51.73,Default,,0,0,0,,then, is a paradigm allegiance.\NAnd people become very disturbed
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.73,1:00:59.21,Default,,0,0,0,,if you try to talk to them about more abstract concepts.\NAnd they'll say that's all, whoa, whoa.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.21,1:01:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a job one time in a clinic.\NI covered for psychiatrists being gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:04.21,1:01:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I covered a clinic in Codwood Friday afternoons\Nbecause they were short of doctors there.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.21,1:01:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the guy who ran the place asked me where I lived,\NI said, uh, it's Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.21,1:01:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, oh, all the woo-woos.\NI had to be careful not to talk about anything
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.55,1:01:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,that wasn't literal concrete.\NHe would think that I'm a woo-woo.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:33.65,1:01:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's true.\NThere are a lot of woo-woos in Sedona.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.05,1:01:46.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They're always seeing flying saucers and stuff.\NThere are a lot of woo-woos in Sedona, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:46.92,1:01:51.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's true.\NAnyway, I'll never forget his saying that.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.40,1:01:54.40,Default,,0,0,0,,He looked at me.\NHe said, woo-woos.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.40,1:02:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the way he said it.\NMeaning not practical, not down to earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.59,1:02:06.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's a certain paradigm allegiance.\NAnd there's a limitation of paradigm of what's possible
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.59,1:02:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and what's real.\NI'm trying to present some work right now to a group
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.76,1:02:20.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that's probably pretty just Newtonian ordinary consciousness\Nthat entails comprehending quantum mechanics.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.76,1:02:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And...\NThe problem is not in explaining it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.63,1:02:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The problem is my understanding how would you present\Nadvanced quantum theory to somebody who is still Newtonian
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.67,1:02:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in their thinking pattern.\NYou see, because when we do consciousness calibration,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.92,1:02:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there's no here and there.\NIn the quantum, infinite quantum reality,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.92,1:02:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,which is identical with consciousness itself,\Nthe field of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.09,1:02:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,there is no here or there.\NThere is no now or then.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.25,1:03:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no future or past.\NAn infinite universe has no center.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.28,1:03:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no middle of everythingness.\NThere's no beginningness.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.28,1:03:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no endingness.\NThere's no here and there.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.28,1:03:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,There's then and now and no future.\NAnd all time is now.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:18.76,1:03:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All time is now.\NAll places are here.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:23.01,1:03:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody get that?\NEverywhere, wherever you are,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:32.80,1:03:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,it's the same as anybody else because\Nhere I'm the center of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.80,1:03:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,in an infinite universe,\Nbut here I'm also in the center of the universe
Dialogue: 0,1:03:40.80,1:03:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,because an infinite universe has no center.\NThat's why consciousness calibration works.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:45.90,1:03:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you're picking up essence,\Nand essence is not dependent on
Dialogue: 0,1:03:51.90,1:03:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,time, location, or causality.\NWith consciousness calibration,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.44,1:04:02.51,Default,,0,0,0,,what you're doing is you're reading the essence\Nof a thing at a distance.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.51,1:04:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,At a distance, you're holding the concept\Nof what I'm looking at right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:07.63,1:04:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I don't have to go from here to there,\Nand I can, because I've done it millions of times,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.76,1:04:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of times, I can just about guess\Nwhat it's going to calibrate.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.80,1:04:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I can just guess because I've done it a lot of times.\NWhat I'm looking at calibrates over 200, 201, 205.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.96,1:04:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What I'm looking at calibrates at 200,\Nis what I got when I looked at it,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:33.44,1:04:37.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the cement pillar.\NThe human body calibrates at 200,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.78,1:04:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so does nature, and so does planet Earth.\NForget the divinity of planet Earth,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.15,1:04:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,it calibrates at 200.\NIt's dirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.17,1:05:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord, oh, dirt.\NWe should lay down human life to serve dirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:04.55,1:05:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Environmentalists, burn up houses,\Nkill people for the sake of dirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.51,1:05:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Dirt.\NDirt's 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.01,1:05:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not worth killing a rabbit for dirt.\NRabbit calibrates harder than dirt.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:21.76,1:05:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The human body, there's no point in worshipping that either.\NThe human body calibrates at exactly 200.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:33.23,1:05:38.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The human body calibrates from dust you arise\Nand from dust you return.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.23,1:05:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So there's no point in being a narcissistic,\Nworshipping the human body and all its glory,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.96,1:06:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and all its glory.\NShe's going to be dust in a few years.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.32,1:06:10.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Came from dust, baby, you're going back to dust,\Nso forget all that fancy stuff, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.40,1:06:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Your body is the same as cement, dirt,\Nroots of weeds.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.32,1:06:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,200, yeah.\N200 is neutral on the level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.76,1:06:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's neutral.\NSo what you make of it is up to you from here.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.98,1:06:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You can plant flowers in it,\Nor you can dump refuse in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:38.07,1:06:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's really respect for your fellow man,\Nnot for the earth.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:45.59,1:06:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of people think that humanity should be eliminated\Nso that we can return the earth to its pristine nature.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.69,1:06:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot of environmentalists think that, you know.\NMan should be destroyed.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.69,1:07:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I think PETA, the guy who founded that,\Nwho's a woo-woo.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.69,1:07:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a real woo-woo.\NIntellectuals.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.17,1:07:11.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a book, Intellectual Morons,\Nwhich I just love the book,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.17,1:07:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,because it just gives you the details\Non idiots that you know are idiots,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.17,1:07:19.32,Default,,0,0,0,,but you didn't know all the details of how the...\NPETA, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:19.32,1:07:24.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We should kill all humans,\Nkill all humans so we can give the world back
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.84,1:07:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,to the dinosaurs, I guess.\NDinosaurs like to eat people.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.80,1:07:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There weren't many people around at the time of dinosaurs.\NThe dinosaurs ate them all.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.63,1:07:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,People are nummy.\NSo let's see.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.07,1:07:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultural norms.\NSo we have paradigm allegiance.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:47.07,1:07:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Cultural norms decide what's right and wrong\Nand unfortunately are also used to define truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.07,1:08:07.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So a cultural norm is very much a propagandized politicalization\Nand therefore what's normal in one environment
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.61,1:08:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,is not normal in another.\NCultural norms.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.86,1:08:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Dictate, then, behaviors.\NSo what would pass as okay on a beach here
Dialogue: 0,1:08:19.86,1:08:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,would get you arrested over in an Arabic country,\Nput away, probably killed,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:24.86,1:08:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,stoned to death, actually.\NYou try that over there and you get put away.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.86,1:08:37.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The allegorical versus the literal,\Nwhich means the letter versus the spirit of the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.69,1:08:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The letter versus the spirit of the law.\NAnd one of the most frequent,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.76,1:08:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,most frequent political tricks\Nis to distort the spirit of the law
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.76,1:08:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,under the guise of being the letter of the law or vice versa.\NThe letter versus the spirit of the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.15,1:09:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, there are signs everywhere.\NIf you see anything suspicious, please report it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.96,1:09:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That instantly brought up, as was put into the design.\NLet's just see if that was a design.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.82,1:09:20.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a conscious design,\Nwhat I'm holding in mind, resist.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.65,1:09:34.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NFive more minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.38,1:09:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,We have five more minutes of what?\NShe's always telling me the end of the world is at hand
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.18,1:09:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and she's always been wrong, you know.\NThe world's going to end in five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.60,1:09:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NAn evolved mind instantly spots fallacy.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.47,1:09:57.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take the flying M.M.s.\NThe flying M.M.s.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:57.47,1:09:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Flying M.M.s.\Nwas complete deception
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.47,1:10:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,from the origination.\NResist.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.47,1:10:06.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all preset.\NCare set up the legal reaction to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.81,1:10:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The whole thing was designed and advanced.\NSo, the thing with the integrious people
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.48,1:10:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is they tend to be naive.\NIf you're not held together by truth,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:17.48,1:10:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,then deviousness becomes a standard tool.\NA standard tool.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.48,1:10:28.68,Default,,0,0,0,,You set these people up to imitate\Nwhat in history was a devastating experience
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.68,1:10:30.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in the United States.\NYou set them up to imitate
Dialogue: 0,1:10:30.68,1:10:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,because you know what the response will be.\NCare already was set up to soothe the people
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.68,1:10:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,who, you know,\Npicture these guys as being dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.68,1:10:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Imitating it to the point of the seat belt extenders.\NThey weren't just wandering down the aisle saying,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.68,1:10:56.52,Default,,0,0,0,,gee, I need a seat belt extender, folks.\NNone of them were fat.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.52,1:11:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the weakness of America is this naiveness.\NIt doesn't think in devious,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:02.72,1:11:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,diabolical terms.\NIt doesn't think how can I set this up
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.03,1:11:13.75,Default,,0,0,0,,so as to create a reaction.\NAnd out of that reaction,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.75,1:11:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't be able to ever finger a terrorist again\Nbecause you'll always be racial profiling.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:21.52,1:11:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,If they're all coming from a certain culture,\Nyou can't say anything about any of them
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.73,1:11:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,without being sued.\NSo, the defenders came up on television the other night
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.96,1:11:37.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and said, yes,\NI love the protection of a court of law.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.72,1:11:40.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You've never been sued, folks.\NYou're going to lose your house.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.72,1:11:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to lose your car.\NThere's going to be arguments.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.72,1:11:49.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You're going to end up with a divorce.\NIt's not whether you're going to win in court.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:49.32,1:11:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Lawyers get $300 an hour.\NWe get billed $300 an hour.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.15,1:12:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They say, can't you fax this guy\Nand tell him, no, we can't do it within 30 days?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:05.11,1:12:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,They do.\NYou get a bill for $80.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:10.35,1:12:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the idea of this new law\Nwas to keep you from being sued
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.51,1:12:21.76,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you don't get wiped out\Nby being sued because you're reporting.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.76,1:12:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All the signs in the airports,\Nthey report anything suspicious, don't they?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.50,1:12:34.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Having a gun in your pocket,\Nis that suspicious?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.21,1:12:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, there you see a naivete sets us up.\NSo, you can see goodness in itself,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.77,1:12:47.77,Default,,0,0,0,,to some degree,\Nbut there's a certain downside
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.77,1:12:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,in that if you just become going to denial\Nbecause of your own good inclinations towards others.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:54.77,1:13:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to be spiritual doesn't mean to be stupid.\NThat's all I'm telling you this morning.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.02,1:13:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,To be stupid doesn't mean you got to be dumb.\NStupid.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.15,1:13:12.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to be blind.\NYou don't have to be ignorant.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.25,1:13:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You can be very bright and alert.\NSo, the more your consciousness evolves,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:16.25,1:13:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the more you're willing to look at the downside of things\Nand say to yourself,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:20.25,1:13:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,hey, looks to me like a setup.\NIt's because you yourself are integrous and honest
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.35,1:13:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that you want to know what the truth is.\NI don't want to make them wrong at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:30.35,1:13:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,On the contrary, I compliment them.\NIt was a beautiful piece of stage work.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:36.35,1:13:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Beautiful. Beautiful.\NIt also tells you how cunning what you're up against.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.05,1:13:46.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The impact, how they would respond,\Nthe legalities, the counter suit.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.07,1:13:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And what you're seeing was totally calculated in advance.\NCompletely calculated in advance.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.31,1:13:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm just saying not to be naive\Njust because you're spiritual.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.63,1:14:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes people are spiritually going to denial and naivete.\NThey're worried about the, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:06.63,1:14:11.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the things that are never going to happen\Nand saving the earth and all those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.63,1:14:19.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we just wanted to use the artistic of truth.\NAnd talk about some of the things in today's world.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.17,1:14:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Because spiritually evolved people and students\Ndon't live in a vacuum.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.17,1:14:29.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't all live in an ashram someplace\Ndetached from the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:29.35,1:14:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We all are subject every day to this pounding by the media\Nand the politicized media.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.35,1:14:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we have, how do you become,\Nhow do you stay in a spiritual alignment with truth
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.35,1:14:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in a world that is not aligned with truth\Nis the problem of modern man.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.35,1:14:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's the subject of the book I'm working on\Nand finishing right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.35,1:14:55.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Spirituality and Modern Man.\NSo, we'll take a break, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:55.48,1:15:08.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hurry, hurry, hurry.\NHurry, hurry, hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.90,1:15:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we've already revealed more than all the world\Nhas known throughout all of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:17.31,1:15:27.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Which is a good start for the morning.\NQuestions arise in people's minds.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.40,1:15:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course we'll have questions\Nand answers this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:30.64,1:15:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,But if there's anything really pressing\Njust put your hand up and we'll stop the locomotive
Dialogue: 0,1:15:36.02,1:15:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and try to handle something pressing.\NPressing, pressing.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:41.36,1:15:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Something that you think would be of interest to the crowd.\NOkay, so where were we on our phantasmagoria?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.19,1:16:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a great aunt who used to call something\Nthat was wonderful a monster polypheme.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.80,1:16:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like a Christmas present you got\Nthat's so big they had a blanket over it
Dialogue: 0,1:16:09.23,1:16:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,like a tricycle or something.\NShe'd say, oh that's probably a monster polypheme.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.76,1:16:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Word she made up.\NA monster polypheme.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:21.14,1:16:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So our work is sort of a monster polypheme.\NSo we talked about paradigm allegiance.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.22,1:16:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,It's difficult to get people who are pedestrian\Nin their thinking below 200
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.35,1:16:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to understand the abstract.\NAbstract.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:40.35,1:16:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if you can't prove it.\NSo a lot of debunkers are there.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.43,1:16:54.46,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the home of debunkers.\NThey're into Newtonian materialistic linearity.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:54.46,1:17:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And anything that goes beyond that\Nthey consider fraudulent.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.52,1:17:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So they set out to debunk it, debunk it.\NI've been debunked all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.64,1:17:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Debunkers.\NOne of the great debunkers is actually a stage
Dialogue: 0,1:17:14.76,1:17:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,magician, a stage magician.\NAnd of course occasionally they are useful.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.23,1:17:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Occasionally they're useful.\NNot that they aren't.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:25.39,1:17:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NSo things have to fall within a certain paradigm
Dialogue: 0,1:17:30.43,1:17:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,to be accepted as possibly real.\NAnd that's pretty much set by your whole culture.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.43,1:17:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The culture in which you grew up.\NThe culture that we are currently bombarded with.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:43.60,1:17:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What is within the norms?\NNow consciousness calibration itself is not within cultural norms.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:50.63,1:17:58.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The world thinks in terms of linear local causality.\NThe fact that you can read the essence of something
Dialogue: 0,1:17:58.01,1:18:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,at a great distance\Nis not within their paradigm of possible.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.17,1:18:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore you would expect criticisms to come from people\Nwho are literal and pedestrian
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.59,1:18:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in their thinking because they're not capable of thinking\Nin abstract terminology.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:16.59,1:18:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,They think in terms of content and not context, etc.\NThe fact that you can read anything anywhere in time.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.61,1:18:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So the thing that's mind-boggling about consciousness calibration\Nis that you can know anything about anything
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.35,1:18:41.27,Default,,0,0,0,,anywhere in time or space\Nso long as you get permission.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:41.27,1:18:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So I tell people when you use it,\NI always ask, I have permission to ask this question.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.51,1:18:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And occasionally you'll get a no.\NI do it silently all the time with Susan
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.51,1:18:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,so as not to take up the audience's time\Nbut I should verbalize it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.85,1:19:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Because occasionally you'll get a no.\NSometimes you can find out the reason for the no
Dialogue: 0,1:19:02.78,1:19:08.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and other times you can't.\NUsually it's very seldom we get a no
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.01,1:19:15.01,Default,,0,0,0,,but many people do get a no.\NAnd one reason you get it is because of karmic reasons.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.01,1:19:20.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason people below 200 can't get the truth\Nwith this methodology
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.01,1:19:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,is because if you follow truth\Nwhat you end up with is God.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.19,1:19:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,God and truth are one and the same thing.\NSo if you're an atheist, you negate God
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.30,1:19:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're not able to do kinesiology.\NAnd some well-known professors
Dialogue: 0,1:19:35.52,1:19:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,who attack kinesiology\NI couldn't figure out why do they
Dialogue: 0,1:19:39.52,1:19:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,he calibrates 190.\NWhy does he calibrate 190?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.52,1:19:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he's an atheist.\NSo then I got why it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.52,1:19:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, we quit using the term.\NWe don't do kinesiology anymore.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:52.90,1:19:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,We just do muscle testing.\NPeople don't like the term so I'll throw it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:02.76,1:20:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I only mentioned the term begin with\Nout of respect for the teacher in which
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.76,1:20:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,whose class I saw how it worked.\NI instantly got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.76,1:20:12.76,Default,,0,0,0,,He saw it as local.\NI saw it as non-local.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.76,1:20:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But I thought I would honor him by that reference.\NHowever, if they don't take it that way
Dialogue: 0,1:20:18.76,1:20:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll win.\NI need kinesiology like a hole in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:26.94,1:20:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Kinesiology actually is muscle testing\Nto diagnose physical conditions
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.94,1:20:34.94,Default,,0,0,0,,by physical response.\NAnd of course we're using it in a different paradigm.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.94,1:20:38.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry I ever brought the word in.\NWe've eliminated it from the reproduction
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.94,1:20:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,of all the new books.\NWe just eliminate it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.94,1:20:47.98,Default,,0,0,0,,If people don't like it, take it out.\NDon't want to offend anyone.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.89,1:21:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so the human mind of course.\NWe talked about hermeneutics of abstraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.85,1:21:07.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Attention set.\NYou can't understand the content
Dialogue: 0,1:21:07.39,1:21:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,unless you add the context.\NIs a certain thing legal and okay in the United States?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.39,1:21:18.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It depends.\NIt depends are you at war or not at war.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.39,1:21:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Certain things went on during World War II.\NAfter the war was over they were eliminated.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.39,1:21:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But they were necessary at the time.\NAnd we did Werner's, Werner Erhard's definition
Dialogue: 0,1:21:31.28,1:21:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,which I always like.\NTrue all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.28,1:21:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,So the understanding depends on your brain physiology,\Nindoctrination, and your paradigms of reality
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.28,1:21:49.82,Default,,0,0,0,,which are a reflection of what's normal in your culture.\NAllegorical versus literal.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.82,1:21:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Letter versus sphere of the law.\NWe gave that example right before the break.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.82,1:22:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Current litigation, the current laws\Nthat are under argumentation.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.82,1:22:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Which to me, try to use the letter of the law\Nto escape the spirit of the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.89,1:22:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So very often the letter of the law\Nis used to defeat the spirit of the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:13.89,1:22:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The spirit of the law,\Nreport anything suspicious in the airport,
Dialogue: 0,1:22:19.68,1:22:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,is quite obvious to see.\NAll right.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.61,1:22:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fallacy of mixing levels\Nis what is true at one level
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.26,1:22:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is not necessarily true at another.\NAnd render unto Caesar that which is Caesar's.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.72,1:22:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And unto God which is God's\Nis a way of expressing the different levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.68,1:22:53.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes we see spiritual error\Nbecause they try to apply a spiritual dictum
Dialogue: 0,1:22:53.68,1:22:58.68,Default,,0,0,0,,which is appropriate in this context\Nbut not appropriate in another context.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.68,1:23:05.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The fallacy of mixing levels.\NThe letter versus the spirit of the law.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:05.72,1:23:11.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The fallacy of mixing levels\Nis the basis for a lot of spiritual error.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:11.23,1:23:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially in New Ages\Nwhen there is a lot of materialism.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.14,1:23:21.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Limitations of science,\Nwe gave the example of junk science.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:21.14,1:23:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And how it becomes politicized,\Nit becomes a whole big world enthusiasm.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.26,1:23:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And mass delusions and madness of crowds\Nis the only way to explain that.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:34.64,1:23:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,People get carried away with grandiosity about it all.\NAnd of course the money pours in.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:39.64,1:23:45.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You have festivals all over the world\Nto overcome something that doesn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:45.82,1:23:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You get a lot of TV coverage.\NPeople do anything to get a few moments on television.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:51.82,1:23:55.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Anything.\NIncluding lying through their teeth.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:55.82,1:24:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so the distortion of relativism,\Nrhetoric and sophistry
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.23,1:24:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,has been noted in ancient Greece.\NAnd therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:06.27,1:24:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,part of being an educated spiritual student\NI think is to have some
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.27,1:24:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,at least superficial understanding\Nof the philosophy of ancient Greece.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.27,1:24:20.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Because our culture is\Na Greco-Judo-Christian.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.27,1:24:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And our emphasis on reason and rationality\Nis part of that ancient tradition.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.27,1:24:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There are whole cultures, you know,\Nwhich are not,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:32.36,1:24:37.43,Default,,0,0,0,,we just presume everybody's like us.\NThere are whole cultures that forbid reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.43,1:24:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We say they're dumb and not reasonable.\NThey forbid reason and the basis is
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.55,1:24:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that reason may interfere with faith.\NIf you start using reason
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.47,1:24:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,on a lot of religious concepts\Nyou throw them out as not being reasonable.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.60,1:25:11.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So reason is seen as a jeopardy to faith.\NNow St. Thomas Aquinas,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:11.93,1:25:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,who was a doctor of divinity,\Nsaid the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:16.47,1:25:25.02,Default,,0,0,0,,That reason supports faith.\NAnd he saw reason and faith supporting each other.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.02,1:25:30.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And it certainly,\Nyou can create a very logical reason
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.92,1:25:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,for divinity and the explanation.\NAdvanced quantum mechanics
Dialogue: 0,1:25:36.92,1:25:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and its theory\Ncertainly supports divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.46,1:25:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,just intrinsically.\NThere's an infinite field of energy
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.46,1:25:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,out of which all arises\Nas a consequence of emergence of potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:25:50.46,1:25:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,in the actuality,\Nwhich is what we've been lecturing
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.46,1:25:59.72,Default,,0,0,0,,since the first lecture.\NThe things don't happen by cause,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:59.72,1:26:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a linear Newtonian causality.\NBut an infinite potentiality
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.93,1:26:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes an actuality\Nwhen local conditions are appropriate.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:07.93,1:26:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So we don't see creation.\NWe don't see evolution.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.71,1:26:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the next lecture.\NI can't talk about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.35,1:26:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So junk science prevails.\NJunk science prevails.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:24.35,1:26:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Because it's politically popular\Nand it's profitable.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.35,1:26:36.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I can get a grant on anything anywhere\Nbecause I know the prejudice
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.35,1:26:42.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and all I have to do is calibrate the review committee\Nand I can get a grant to study anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.35,1:26:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because what I do is I put the end result that they want\Nand I say, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.42,1:26:52.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a secondhand smoke will cause crib deaths,\Ncause psoriasis in old people.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.77,1:26:55.77,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what I want to write,\NI can get a grant for it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:55.77,1:27:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can't run your department\Nor university without a grant.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.47,1:27:05.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't keep your position as a professor\Nunless you write papers.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.47,1:27:08.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see how it's rigged.\NYou've got to write papers,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.47,1:27:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to get a grant.\NTo get a grant,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:10.47,1:27:12.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you've got to write something politically pleasing\Nin order to get the money,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.47,1:27:21.64,Default,,0,0,0,,so you tell them what they want to hear.\NThe distortion of relativism,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:21.64,1:27:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,it's said we've already had a whole lecture on relativism\Nand its expression as rhetoric and sophistry.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:27.64,1:27:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And why it contributes so heavily\Nto the decline of current academia.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:35.27,1:27:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the energy field.\NSomebody argued with me in a previous lecture about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.61,1:27:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's look at the Duke University incident.\NThe Duke University incident.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:50.84,1:27:59.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Three innocent men, proven innocent by DNA.\NA faculty of 87 members signed a denunciation
Dialogue: 0,1:27:59.06,1:28:04.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of these three men.\NThree young men, convicting them in advance,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.84,1:28:10.11,Default,,0,0,0,,even though the DNA layer proved them\Nnot only innocent but impossible
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.11,1:28:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,for them to have been the ones.\NNow, it's bad enough that that condemnation
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.76,1:28:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,was racist and sexist.\NLet's calibrate the Duke University 87 professors.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.78,1:28:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrate over 120, 140, 135.\NCalibrate 135.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:31.94,1:28:35.23,Default,,0,0,0,,People would dispute with me\Nwhether academia has fallen.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:35.23,1:28:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The entire Duke...\N135.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:44.07,1:28:49.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Duke University faculty\Nall signed their names for posterity,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.07,1:28:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrated at 135.\NAll right, after the three gentlemen
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.86,1:29:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,were proven innocent via DNA,\Nand the guy who first prosecuted them
Dialogue: 0,1:29:02.64,1:29:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought was gonna get defrocked.\NAnyway, God knows what'll come of it all.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.64,1:29:12.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Having been proven wrong,\Ndid the Duke faculty retract?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.05,1:29:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,They did not.\NNot only dishonest to begin with and warped,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.46,1:29:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,but totally lacking in integrity.\NAs an academic, if I made a mistake,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.46,1:29:25.46,Default,,0,0,0,,the first thing I'm gonna tell you,\NI'll tell you it's a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:25.46,1:29:29.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like I'm telling you this morning,\NI never used the word kinesiology.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:29.46,1:29:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,It throws people in the wrong direction.\NSo why not admit a mistake, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.31,1:29:40.31,Default,,0,0,0,,carried away by the enthusiasm\Nand the fun of making people wrong, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.31,1:29:45.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Think of all that sexism in there.\NPoor black girl. Poor black girl.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.31,1:29:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Abused by these rich white boys.\NThey just jumped on that wagon.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:49.42,1:29:54.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It was so tempting.\NGotta condemn these bad...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:54.42,1:29:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, it isn't, you know,\Nmaking a mistake is one thing,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:58.44,1:30:02.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in the poor judgment of the...\NBut not retracting it later.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:02.44,1:30:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,To this day, they have not retracted it.\NSo we got what the condemnation calibrated, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:30:08.55,1:30:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The failure to retract.\NThe failure to retract that.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:13.80,1:30:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Calibrates over 90, 95.\NTo say it in the first place is 135.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.63,1:30:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,To not retract it is 95.\NOne of the commandments, one of the Ten Commandments,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:29.22,1:30:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,which is enough to make every politician shudder,\Nis to bear false witness against your brother.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:38.43,1:30:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,To bear false witness\Nis breaking one of the Ten Commandments.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.53,1:30:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't think people should just break\Nthe Ten Commandments willy-nilly
Dialogue: 0,1:30:48.56,1:30:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and then consider themselves politically superior\Nthat they've done so, or lead, or something.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:56.14,1:31:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's why academia has gone down.\NThat's just a typical example, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.42,1:31:13.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But the politicalization of just about everything\Ninsinuates itself into such things as...
Dialogue: 0,1:31:13.06,1:31:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What do they call it? Radical math now.\NYou don't add up two things.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.06,1:31:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Two plus two plus two.\NYou add up two starving Africans.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:24.40,1:31:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Two starving African white or dark ladies.\NAnd then you come up with social injustice.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:36.18,1:31:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,What the mentally impaired don't get\Nis that this is an unjust world.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.11,1:31:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all born unequal.\NThere's not two people in here that are equal.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.06,1:31:58.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born tall and handsome.\NAnd then there's short guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:01.88,1:32:05.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Some people are born rich.\NThey used to come up to school in a Cadillac.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:05.88,1:32:07.88,Default,,0,0,0,,We had a little old used car,\Nand I'd tell my dad,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.88,1:32:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,drop me off in the block away.\NThe kids are all going to jeer at you.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:13.68,1:32:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't have any money,\Nso my grandmother knit me sweaters.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.31,1:32:21.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what they did?\NThey'd grab the back of your sweater
Dialogue: 0,1:32:21.31,1:32:26.34,Default,,0,0,0,,and look to see if there was a lapel there,\Nand say, oh, his mother made it.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:26.34,1:32:33.85,Default,,0,0,0,,So nowadays a handmade sweater costs you a couple hundred.\NAnd a machine made one.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:34.85,1:32:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But in those days the status was\Nnothing in this world is created equal, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:44.01,1:32:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can't chop all the tall people off at the legs.\NRemember the war in Africa,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:52.07,1:32:57.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the Bantu against the Watussis?\NAnd the Bantu that were the midges,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:57.30,1:33:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the small ones, right?\NThey cut the Watussis' legs off
Dialogue: 0,1:33:00.30,1:33:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,so they'd be the same height.\NOh, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:07.51,1:33:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So what the far left politically doesn't get\Nis that we are created equal,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:11.51,1:33:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and we're all unequal,\Nand it's not anybody's fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.51,1:33:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just the way it is.\NIt doesn't have to make it somebody's fault.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:19.72,1:33:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point to create a finger.\NYou try to find what is the basis
Dialogue: 0,1:33:23.72,1:33:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,of what can be corrected,\Nand you correct it.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:25.72,1:33:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,You correct it.\NSome people are born with very high IQs,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:28.72,1:33:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and other people are not.\NThat's why the far left does not like
Dialogue: 0,1:33:32.72,1:33:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole subject of IQ.\NSome kids should follow an academic road
Dialogue: 0,1:33:39.10,1:33:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,and others should follow a vocational road.\NI mean, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:45.51,1:33:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd rather be a well-to-do machinist\Nthan a broke college dropout.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:51.67,1:33:55.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The last time I had something made\Nby a machinist in Flagstaff,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:55.07,1:33:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it cost me a fortune.\NI wanted a couple of four-inch bearings
Dialogue: 0,1:33:58.56,1:34:02.56,Default,,0,0,0,,made for a great big waterwheel.\NI had to have them special made.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.56,1:34:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell you,\Nmachinists make plenty of money.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:08.94,1:34:10.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't buy it at Walmart,\Ndon't get a machinist.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:12.46,1:34:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, so what is truth?\NTruth is subject to programming
Dialogue: 0,1:34:17.28,1:34:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and indoctrination.\NThe hermeneutics of abstraction,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:21.47,1:34:27.38,Default,,0,0,0,,it's limited by attention set.\NWe talked about the letter
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.38,1:34:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,versus the spirit of the law,\Nthe fallacy of mixing levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:31.38,1:34:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,See, what is truth in one paradigm\Nis not true in another.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:36.38,1:34:43.40,Default,,0,0,0,,What's fair and equal in one sub-level of society\Nis not fair and equal in another.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:43.40,1:34:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't just sort people\Naccording to race, sex, age,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:47.40,1:34:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,gender and all that kind of stuff\Nbecause you're mixing levels.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.53,1:34:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then we talked about junk science\Nand its popularization.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.53,1:35:00.72,Default,,0,0,0,,It's very, very big payoff.\NDistortion of relativism,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:00.72,1:35:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,we already covered with the whole lecture.\NAnd as compared to absolutism,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:06.76,1:35:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and I got a kick out of some critic\Nthat wrote something about to warn them,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:11.76,1:35:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,warn them,\Nabout the books I write,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.76,1:35:16.76,Default,,0,0,0,,warning,\Nyou're warned in advance
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.76,1:35:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,that he's an absolutist.\NWarning, he's an absolutist.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.80,1:35:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,A bad word.\NA bad word means you don't,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.39,1:35:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you're not run by relativism.\NIt means the truth is not just what you think it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.39,1:35:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And it opposes the narcissistic position\Nthat if I think it or believe it,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:39.50,1:35:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it must be true.\NAnd it denies the existence of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:43.76,1:35:50.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Which of course is the whole basis of absolutism.\NYes, there is an absolute scale.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.85,1:35:54.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And in fact,\Nthe calibrated levels of consciousness are absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:54.85,1:36:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They absolutely go from one to a thousand.\NAnd they absolutely calibrate God at infinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.07,1:36:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough to boil the blood of any relativist.\NWe'll move on to the next one.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:10.07,1:36:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,How many slides do we have on truth?\NAnd don't lie to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:14.68,1:36:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,How many?\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.60,1:36:23.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.\NThat tells me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:23.23,1:36:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
